The President released a statement praising the FCC's decision on net neutrality. He believes that this decision will preserve the openness and freedom of the internet, while also encouraging innovation, protecting consumer choice, and defending free speech. The President sees this decision as an important part of his strategy to promote American innovation, economic growth, and job creation. He also pledged to continue preserving the freedom and openness of the internet, ensuring that innovation is allowed to thrive and consumers are protected. The President congratulated the FCC and its Chairman, Julius Genachowski, as well as Congressman Henry Waxman, for their work in achieving this important goal.